Date: May 19, 2013
Source: OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=13450


Vesicular stomatitis [VS], Belize
-----------------------
Information received on 19 May 2013 from Dr Miguel Angel Depaz, Director of Animal Health, Animal Health Department, Belize Agricultural Health Authority (BAHA), Belmopan, Belize

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 May 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 May 2013
Report date: 19 May 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 19 May 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 13 Jan 2012 [refers to outbreak of Dec.2011 -- see Comment]
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Vesicular stomatitis virus
Serotype: New Jersey
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Martz Farm, Benque, Waterhole, Cayo
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 May 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 15 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Horses kept for horseback riding at tourist resort in forested area

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 15 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 6.67 percent / 0.00 percent / 0.00 percent / 0.00 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection:
* Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Sporadic outbreaks usually occur during the dry season.

Control measures:
Measures applied
* Quarantine
* Vaccination prohibited
* Treatment of affected animals (local herbal medicine)

Measures to be applied
* No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Laboratory of Diagnosis of Vesicular Diseases (LADIVES) (Regional Reference Laboratory) / Equidae / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 8 May 2013 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [To find the location of this outbreak, go to the top of the OIE site, where there is a map. The farm is near the western border of Belize with Guatemala. - Mod.MHJ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The last outbreaks of VS in Belize were in 2011: in February and March 2011, there were 8 outbreaks in Cayo involving 57 cattle and one horse; in February 2011, a single outbreak in Stan Creek involving 7 pigs; and in December 2011, a single outbreak in Belize involving 6 cattle. All involved the New Jersey strain of the virus. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1AYt.]
